xts like DVD bonus materials for The Lord of the Rings, spoilers for Lost, the opening credits of The Simpsons, Star Wars actions figures, press reviews for Friday Night Lights, the framing of Batman Begins, the videogame of The Thing, and the trailers for The Sweet Hereafter. Plucking these extra materials from the wings and giving them the spotlight they deserve, Jonathan Gray examines the world of film and television that exists before and after the show.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAdvertisingxMotion picturesxSocial aspects. 0aAdvertisingxTelevision programsxSocial aspects. 0aIntertextuality. 0aMass media and culture. 0aMotion picturesxMarketingxSocial aspects. 0aParatext. 0aTelevision programsxMarketingxSocial aspects. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Psychopathology / Dissociative Identity Disorder.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814733158.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814733158zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814733158/original  a978-3-11-070644-4 New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA